communications.communication:
Dear Mr. Wyatt,

Thank you again for your assistance with my FOIA request. Given your request for specificity, I will consolidate several planned additional FOIA requests into this one. Below is a detailed clarification addressing your requirement for specificity under Virginia FOIA § 2.2-3704 B:

Timeframe:
	•	January 1, 2022 to present.

Requested Document Types:
	•	Emails, letters, text messages, handwritten or typed notes, memos, meeting agendas, minutes, calendar invitations, transcripts, and audio recordings.

Specific VMI Officials Included:
	•	All members of the VMI Board of Visitors, including current, former, and those appointed but not confirmed by the Virginia Senate.
	•	Superintendent’s Office staff and senior administrators, specifically including those in policymaking roles related to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) or Diversity, Opportunity, and Inclusion (DOI).

External Individuals and Organizations Specifically Included:
	•	Bert Ellis (Jefferson Council/UVA Board);
	•	Tom Neale (Jefferson Council/AFSA);
	•	Tom Rideout (The General’s Redoubt);
	•	Matt Daniel (Spirit of VMI PAC);
	•	Jim Bacon (AFSA/Bacon’s Rebellion);
	•	Thomas Gottwald (in external contexts related to named organizations prior to his appointment to the BoV);
	•	Theodore Adams III (as lobbyist);
	•	Frank Atkinson, James Dyke, Fran Bradford, Laura Novey (McGuireWoods Consulting lobbyists retained by the Alumni Institute Foundation), and identifiable intermediaries;
	•	Richard Cullen; 
        •       The Governor’s Office or Secretary of the Commonwealth;
	•	Explicit representatives (official or grassroots) affiliated with:
	•	Alumni Free Speech Alliance (AFSA);
	•	Spirit of VMI PAC;
	•	Jefferson Council (UVA);
	•	American Council of Trustees and Alumni (ACTA);
	•	The General’s Redoubt (W&L);
	•	The Cadet Foundation (limited to policy or governance discussions not previously made public via FOIA).

Additional Requested Communications:
	•	Relevant communications involving John Adams, the VMI Board of Visitors, and Rep. Ben Cline’s office related to Adams’ conversations with Senator Jennifer Carroll Foy, explicitly including any audio recordings, transcripts, or other records  Adams made of these conversations.

Specific Topics Requested:
	•	DEI/DOI policies, programs, initiatives, or discussions;
	•	Academic freedom, “free speech,” or related controversies;
	•	VMI Board of Visitors appointments, confirmations, or governance changes;
	•	Coordination or strategic advocacy involving listed external entities or individuals;
	•	Financial records or donor correspondence explicitly tied to DEI/DOI policies, or communications with donors referencing conditions related to DEI initiatives, Superintendent Wins, removal of the Jackson Statue, or other relevant reforms during Maj. Gen. Cedric Wins’ tenure.

Explicitly Excluded:
	•	Documents from the known 1st Amendment lawsuit involving The Cadet Foundation (Robert Morris) that have already been publicly released through FOIA;
	•	General editorial, fundraising, advertising, or routine operational communications unrelated to the governance or policy topics above.

Please inform me if any additional clarification is necessary. Thank you again for your cooperation and assistance.

Respectfully,
In Alma Maters Name
